Description: Corroded copper alloy arrow-head of rhombic cross-section with a long and thick tang of round cross-section..
Curator's comments: On bronze arrow heads, see W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 78 § 77.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 78 § 77)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.71, p.183, pl.25)
